INSERT INTO `word_info` VALUES ('a great deal','None','https://dictionary.blob.core.chinacloudapi.cn/media/audio/tom/95/a9/95A9871BBE9DFE523C5702ACB3C858D2.mp3','adv.','非常；极其','','','','','','','Though as a child I used to play with my brothers and sisters, I spent a great deal of time by myself, and I always felt apart, alone.','虽然我小时候总是和兄弟姐妹一起玩儿，但我很多时候是独自一人的，我总是感到我是分离的，单独的。','https://dictionary.blob.core.chinacloudapi.cn/media/audio/tom/95/4d/954DE81FE215B34F91E2E830F43EB3BA.mp3'),('a pivotal figure','','','','','','','','','','','The England star proved a pivotal figure for Chelsea as they clinched the Premiership title in devastating style last term.','这位英国巨星用上个赛季率领球队势如破竹夺取联赛冠军的成绩来表明他是切尔西的枢纽人物。','https://dictionary.blob.core.chinacloudapi.cn/media/audio/tom/0d/dd/0DDD275E579601452D85D74219FCCEB9.mp3'),('abandon','ə\'bændən','https://dictionary.blob.core.chinacloudapi.cn/media/audio/tom/ff/cd/FFCDA07EC24EE4DCB12E0A6C57392CF2.mp3','v.','放弃；抛弃；废弃；遗弃','n.','放肆；狂热；任性；恣意任性','','','','','Love, can\'t easy to do, loved and then do not abandon; feeling, can\'t move literally, move and then can\'t regret.','爱，不能轻易，爱了就不要放弃；情，不能妄动，动了就不能后悔。','https://dictionary.blob.core.chinacloudapi.cn/media/audio/tom/d7/d7/D7D73815EF04C2D2C51460489F4E64A7.mp3'),('abandoned','ə\'bændənd','https://dictionary.blob.core.chinacloudapi.cn/media/audio/tom/19/66/196622DA1C88169E391DE05E23AD7228.mp3','adj.','被放弃[扔弃,遗弃]了的；无耻的；不可救药的；报废的','','','','','','','In England, he had been working in nightclubs and bars, he said, when he met a group of people who squatted in abandoned buildings.','在英国的时候，他在夜总会和酒吧工作过，他说，当他发现一群废弃楼盘的非法占据者。','https://dictionary.blob.core.chinacloudapi.cn/media/audio/tom/32/9f/329FBFEAEBA0E0BD440C2DA6EB50C9A7.mp3'),('abbreviate','əˈbriːviːeɪt','https://dictionary.blob.core.chinacloudapi.cn/media/audio/tom/4d/2c/4D2CFAD424397974543E1CB3991A1661.mp3','v.','缩写；缩短；缩写为；简称','','','','','','','The clergyman would only absolve his torturers , abbreviate none of his final words which once more called on the abolition of slavery.','这位牧师只会赦免折磨他的那些人的罪恶，他不会简化最后的话语，它们会再次用来号召废除奴隶制。','https://dictionary.blob.core.chinacloudapi.cn/media/audio/tom/81/b5/81B5248660BA06623E63EB1B2E4BB721.mp3'),('abbreviation','əˌbri:vi\'eɪʃn','https://dictionary.blob.core.chinacloudapi.cn/media/audio/tom/64/5d/645D43586B1E0EAC657AC3D133434744.mp3','n.','缩写；【数学】约分；【音乐】略号；〔数〕约分','','','','','','','And soon OK was to find its place in many languages as a reminder of a familiar word or abbreviation.','很快OK就在不同语言中作为某个常见单词或缩写词的提示语存在。','https://dictionary.blob.core.chinacloudapi.cn/media/audio/tom/86/16/8616B16DEB943BC5E927A540DB0A2F13.mp3'),('abide','əˈbaɪd','https://dictionary.blob.core.chinacloudapi.cn/media/audio/tom/6a/1e/6A1E702DA4A876832B0DAF07657B79F2.mp3','v.','容忍；等候；逗留；居留','','','','','','','The company has also preferred to leave the matter to the courts, promising to abide by their decisions.','公司也希望将这个棘手问题交与法院处理，并承诺遵守判决。','https://dictionary.blob.core.chinacloudapi.cn/media/audio/tom/f9/01/F901AC4108D2BD06D4ABDDAAE0656F33.mp3'),('abiding','ə\'baɪdɪŋ','https://dictionary.blob.core.chinacloudapi.cn/media/audio/tom/05/cd/05CD4E9C8F30ECEA6E363F918FE36BCF.mp3','adj.','〔书面语〕持久的；永久的；由来已久的','','','','','','','There was just one problem, which hadn\'t occurred to his handlers - Uri was a vegetarian with an abiding respect for all life.','只是有一点是其上司没有想到的——尤里是个历来尊重一切生命的素食主义者。','https://dictionary.blob.core.chinacloudapi.cn/media/audio/tom/8c/63/8C634B5C4A730CC91ED47B0AE6471F75.mp3'),('ability','ə\'bɪləti','https://dictionary.blob.core.chinacloudapi.cn/media/audio/tom/10/9e/109EEBF50AE237FC182C0307980E87D3.mp3','n.','能力；能够；才能；能干','','','','','','','All this leads to fewer cravings for sugar and the body\'s ability to handle it as well.','这些都有助于减少吃糖的欲望和提高身体的处理能力。','https://dictionary.blob.core.chinacloudapi.cn/media/audio/tom/f0/9f/F09F007EF338D47DF668E784A4A2C9F1.mp3'),('ablaze','əˈbleɪz','https://dictionary.blob.core.chinacloudapi.cn/media/audio/tom/6c/ea/6CEADBC561E90A5C175A2626028A55D5.mp3','adj.','着火的；发亮的；发光的；大动肝火','','','','','','','While his clothes ablaze, the flames shot from his waist to well over his head.','衣服着火了，火苗迅速从他的腰蹿过他的头。','https://dictionary.blob.core.chinacloudapi.cn/media/audio/tom/3d/de/3DDE2664029883FF74E88C6072F12C19.mp3'),('able','None','https://dictionary.blob.core.chinacloudapi.cn/media/audio/tom/43/df/43DF4BD3BAEAB0B6E67B8BE674F19555.mp3','adj.','会；有为；〔接不定式〕能；有才能的','','','','','','','I can not help but think of home in front of the Chrysanthemum Cong do not know if it can no longer be able to sprout.','我不禁想起家门前的那丛菊花，不知它还能不能再萌芽。','https://dictionary.blob.core.chinacloudapi.cn/media/audio/tom/c8/6d/C86D1C81DB690CC3B6CC9C8AE6745D53.mp3'),('abnormal','æbˈnɒrm(ə)l','https://dictionary.blob.core.chinacloudapi.cn/media/audio/tom/10/b9/10B902FA30BC14FAF2FA197C7A849AA4.mp3','adj.','畸形的','','','','','','','\"Still think it\'s abnormal? \" I asked. She did not. And then she did me, again; but this time all on her own.','“还觉得这不正常吗？”我问到。她当然不觉得了。然后她又让我达到了高潮，这次完全是她自己做的。','https://dictionary.blob.core.chinacloudapi.cn/media/audio/tom/3a/15/3A1551D3EAF8A95669AE73B29CFE8D73.mp3'),('aboard','ə\'bɔ:d','https://dictionary.blob.core.chinacloudapi.cn/media/audio/tom/dd/f2/DDF2AA7102A7183BC92493F8A0197759.mp3','adv.','上船[飞机,车]；靠船边；在船上；在…上','prep.','上车；在船[飞机,车]上','','','','','I once read in a magazine in Beijing about a man aboard a train who had been accosted by an old woman when the train stopped at a station.','我曾经在北京的杂志上看过一则女人在火车进站的时候向车上的一个男人卖东西的故事。','https://dictionary.blob.core.chinacloudapi.cn/media/audio/tom/bb/13/BB137519E1649662203B7BAD58923BCB.mp3'),('abolish','None','https://dictionary.blob.core.chinacloudapi.cn/media/audio/tom/4d/cd/4DCD18CAF693AA4E36B0558663DBA616.mp3','v.','废除；消灭；撤销','','','','','','','It\'s scandalous that in 13 years of power New Labour did not abolish the charitable status of public schools.','新工党在位的13年里没有取消公立学校的慈善状况简直就是丑闻。','https://dictionary.blob.core.chinacloudapi.cn/media/audio/tom/c6/fd/C6FDD3DBCE8B49BD746FE12C5305871D.mp3'),('abolition','.æbə\'lɪʃ(ə)n','https://dictionary.blob.core.chinacloudapi.cn/media/audio/tom/ee/59/EE59C0D373A834421CC43801565513E5.mp3','n.','废止','','','','','','','He gave no timetable for its abolition but said he would ask Her Majesty\'s Revenue & Customs to assess how much money it actually raises.','他并没有给出废止该税率的时间表，但他说将要求英国税务及海关来评估废止的作用，以及将会给国家财政带来的利益。','https://dictionary.blob.core.chinacloudapi.cn/media/audio/tom/b5/3c/B53C62392103A1079FCAE8045FEFB67B.mp3'),('abolitionist','.æbə\'lɪʃ(ə)nɪst','https://dictionary.blob.core.chinacloudapi.cn/media/audio/tom/8b/4e/8B4E4543D656B8169EE4AAF82B1C7023.mp3','n.','主张废除…的人','','','','','','','Such was the general political and economic picture in the United States when the abolitionist movement began to make itself felt.','这就是废奴运动开始时美国的政治和经济现状。','https://dictionary.blob.core.chinacloudapi.cn/media/audio/tom/a2/f8/A2F8C3DEDFEFD788452E35A927CDD63F.mp3'),('abort','əˈbɔː(r)t','https://dictionary.blob.core.chinacloudapi.cn/media/audio/tom/f1/ef/F1EF4E0519BA27380F2AF932B2D48771.mp3','v.','中止；流产；放弃；堕胎','n.','流产；放弃；〈比喻〉未做好的打算；未成形的计划','','','','','Every single goal I\'ve ever accomplished has been a direct result of her decision to not abort me and to give me to my family.','她没有打掉我的决定使我完成了一个目标，就是我拥有了现在的家庭。','https://dictionary.blob.core.chinacloudapi.cn/media/audio/tom/9e/e0/9EE040005D546CDE35B8556EBD1684A3.mp3'),('abortion','ə\'bɔ:ʃn','https://dictionary.blob.core.chinacloudapi.cn/media/audio/tom/e6/4a/E64AC2BA6DD72ED27FEB752F71D2F056.mp3','n.','流产；堕胎；败育；失败','','','','','','','Isn\'t it just a little ironic to see a group of pro-lifers throwing eggs at an abortion clinic?','那些反堕胎人士朝人流诊所砸鸡蛋是不是有点挖苦？','https://dictionary.blob.core.chinacloudapi.cn/media/audio/tom/3a/66/3A6666A57432863D2BA0C2A5EAD876E7.mp3'),('abound','ə\'baʊnd','https://dictionary.blob.core.chinacloudapi.cn/media/audio/tom/b0/36/B036E0E078A5281A95E9024287B7635F.mp3','v.','大量存在；有许多','','','','','','','Yet misfortunes, hardships and temptations abound in life. Trying to stay peaceful in a world of so many noises is hard indeed.','生活中真的有太多的烦恼，困难和诱惑，要想风不止我亦要静真的很难很难。','https://dictionary.blob.core.chinacloudapi.cn/media/audio/tom/2c/49/2C49B3156EB1694FF1D12136F46AB878.mp3'),('abrasion','None','https://dictionary.blob.core.chinacloudapi.cn/media/audio/tom/8a/b7/8AB7E18F625AD1C6ADB6EA55BE38579B.mp3','n.','磨损；磨蚀；磨去；擦去','','','','','','','Despite these lower velocities, there appeared to be evidence for the operation of impact-abrasion phenomena in such situations.','尽管有这些速度低，出现了以证据为操作冲击磨损现象，在这种形势。这些证据分为若干领域，下面讨论。','https://dictionary.blob.core.chinacloudapi.cn/media/audio/tom/5f/8f/5F8F838AC8A8B702E92980C40A4F5B85.mp3'),('abrasive','None','https://dictionary.blob.core.chinacloudapi.cn/media/audio/tom/a2/35/A235BE9FE47CF591D5E2B0AE0D8A2DAF.mp3','n.','磨料','adj.','有剥蚀作用的；引起摩擦的；磨蚀的；含磨料的','','','','','The presence of striation area is one of the main characteristic on the surface generated by abrasive jet .','波纹区域的存在是磨料射流切割表面的主要特征之一。','https://dictionary.blob.core.chinacloudapi.cn/media/audio/tom/e0/02/E002C00719A97414288D90F5AFD88079.mp3'),('abroad','ə\'brɔ:d','https://dictionary.blob.core.chinacloudapi.cn/media/audio/tom/4a/5d/4A5D7F3EE30712A1896EDB52C6AFD371.mp3','adv.','国外；海外；出国；到国外','','','','','','','The concern (posed by the Economist piece) that this proposed ban would be might be \"misunderstood abroad, \" seems foolish.','该提议使人担心的（Economist文章所提出的），是禁令可能会被「外国误解」，这似乎很荒谬。','https://dictionary.blob.core.chinacloudapi.cn/media/audio/tom/93/d3/93D32F96FEBAC56668EEEA5918D04CE2.mp3'),('abrupt','əˈbrʌpt','https://dictionary.blob.core.chinacloudapi.cn/media/audio/tom/5b/0e/5B0EC91850FD0306E17C0322889FAD30.mp3','adj.','粗鲁；粗暴；突然的；突如其来的','','','','','','','She walks over to her usual group but when she tries to talk to any of them, their responses are abrupt and unfriendly.','她回到原来的朋友中想和她们说话时，朋友的反应很突然也不友好。','https://dictionary.blob.core.chinacloudapi.cn/media/audio/tom/d7/56/D75626EBECD7EFF0DED181F8FC3341BA.mp3'),('absence','\'æbsəns','https://dictionary.blob.core.chinacloudapi.cn/media/audio/tom/46/13/46136587D116A95087E84D90CBEEA0ED.mp3','n.','缺席；缺乏；不在；不存在','','','','','','','But scientists have now found a quasar that\'s apparently churning out new stars in the absence of a host galaxy.','但是现在科学家们发现，一颗没有挂靠主星系的类星体显然在大量地制造出新恒星。','https://dictionary.blob.core.chinacloudapi.cn/media/audio/tom/a7/db/A7DBB2830AE563769B07B4E9FD027686.mp3'),('absent','None','https://dictionary.blob.core.chinacloudapi.cn/media/audio/tom/0c/35/0C35629ED4B8B7CD2EB9A2631710864D.mp3','adj.','没有；无；离开；缺勤的','v.','使缺席','','','','','She longed to enquire of the housekeeper whether her master were really absent, but had not courage for it.','她真想问问这位管家奶奶，主人是否真不在家，可是她没有勇气，只得作罢。','https://dictionary.blob.core.chinacloudapi.cn/media/audio/tom/bb/e8/BBE84EA6BE1A6B9B35E96D41BC6109BD.mp3'),('absentee','.æbsən\'ti','https://dictionary.blob.core.chinacloudapi.cn/media/audio/tom/ad/f9/ADF9BED5A885E056A98E732E1300F7C8.mp3','n.','缺席者；缺勤者；缺课者','','','','','','','Although, he admits he would like to see long-term absentee Robin van Persie back in action.','虽然，他承认他也希望在长期缺席名单中的罗宾&#183;范佩西能够火线归来。','https://dictionary.blob.core.chinacloudapi.cn/media/audio/tom/09/56/0956F4C56BAE373174034A00902ABF5A.mp3'),('absenteeism','ˌæbsənˈtiˌɪzəm','https://dictionary.blob.core.chinacloudapi.cn/media/audio/tom/78/49/7849730753632B2164B9D5FCCB27E75C.mp3','n.','(故意)旷工；旷课','','','','','','','A mere reduction absenteeism does not provide solid evidence for the proposition that robots would be better than humans for factory work.','纯粹减少旷工现象不足以提供有力的证据，来证明机器人比人类能更好地从事工厂工作这一命题。','https://dictionary.blob.core.chinacloudapi.cn/media/audio/tom/38/10/38103B17120FF0EC97365EBC13F13978.mp3'),('absolute','.æbsə\'lut','https://dictionary.blob.core.chinacloudapi.cn/media/audio/tom/14/bf/14BF38525B24642E6A24BC452DFE7C23.mp3','adj.','完全的；全部的；绝对的；（口语中尤用以强调）道地的','n.','绝对（指思想或原理）','','','','','The absolute truth of this may be in dispute, but the very nature of glob